obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12897)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12897&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Protection of Women`
  line `from Domestic Violence Act, 2005.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2. 26th October, 2006, vide notification No. S.O. 1776(E), dated by 17th October, 2006, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12898)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12898&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "aggrieved person" means any woman who is, or has been, in a domestic relationship with`
  line `the respondent and who alleges to have been subjected to any act of domestic violence by the`
  line respondent;
  line
  line `(b) "child" means any person below the age of eighteen years and includes any adopted, step or`
  line `foster child;`
  line
  line `(c) "compensation order" means an order granted in terms of section 22;`
  line
  line `(d) "custody order" means an order granted in terms of section 21;`
  line
  line `(e) "domestic incident report" means a report made in the prescribed form on receipt of a`
  line `complaint of domestic violence from an aggrieved person;`
  line
  line `(f) "domestic relationship" means a relationship between two persons who live or have, at any`
  line `point of time, lived together in a shared household, when they are related by consanguinity, marriage,`
  line `or through a relationship in the nature of marriage, adoption or are family members living together as`
  line `a joint family;`
  line
  line `(g) "domestic violence" has the same meaning as assigned to it in section 3;`
  line
  line `(h) "dowry" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 2 of the Dowry Prohibition`
  line `Act, 1961 (28 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(i) "Magistrate" means the Judicial Magistrate of the first class, or as the case may be, the`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrate, exercising jurisdiction under the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973(2 of 1974) in the area where the aggrieved person resides temporarily or otherwise or the`
  line `respondent resides or the domestic violence is alleged to have taken place;`
  line
  line `(j) "medical facility' means such facility as may be notified by the State Government to be a`
  line `medical facility for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "monetary relief" means the compensation which the Magistrate may order the respondent to`
  line `pay to the aggrieved person, at any stage during the hearing of an application seeking any relief under`
  line `this Act, to meet the expenses incurred and the losses suffered by the aggrieved person as a result of`
  line `the domestic violence;`
  line
  line `(l) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `"notified" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(m) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "Protection Officer" means an officer appointed by the State Government under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(o) "protection order" means an order made in terms of section 18;`
  line
  line `(p) "residence order" means an order granted in terms of sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(q) "respondent" means any adult male person who is, or has been, in a domestic relationship`
  line `with the aggrieved person and against whom the aggrieved person has sought any relief under this`
  line `Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that an aggrieved wife or female living in a relationship in the nature of a marriage may`
  line `also file a complaint against a relative of the husband or the male partner;`
  line
  line `(r) "service provider" means an entity registered under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(s) "shared household" means a household where the person aggrieved lives or at any stage has`
  line `lived in a domestic relationship either singly or along with the respondent and includes such a house`
  line `hold whether owned or tenanted either jointly by the aggrieved person and the respondent, or owned`
  line `or tenanted by either of them in respect of which either the aggrieved person or the respondent or both`
  line `jointly or singly have any right, title, interest or equity and includes such a household which may`
  line `belong to the joint family of which the respondent is a member, irrespective of whether the`
  line `respondent or the aggrieved person has any right, title or interest in the shared household;`
  line
  line `(t) "shelter home" means any shelter home as may be notified by the State Government to be as`
  line `helter home for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12899)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Definition of domestic violence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12899&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act, any act, omission or commission`
  line `or conduct of the respondent shall constitute domestic violence in case it--`
  line
  line `(a) harms or injures or endangers the health, safety, life, limb or well-being, whether mental or`
  line `physical, of the aggrieved person or tends to do so and includes causing physical abuse, sexual abuse,`
  line `verbal and emotional abuse and economic abuse; or`
  line
  line `(b) harasses, harms, injures or endangers the aggrieved person with a view to coerce her or any`
  line `other person related to her to meet any unlawful demand for any dowry or other property or valuable`
  line `security; or`
  line
  line `(c) has the effect of threatening the aggrieved person or any person related to her by any conduct`
  line `mentioned in clause (a) or clause (b); or`
  line
  line `(d) otherwise injures or causes harm, whether physical or mental, to the aggrieved person.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "physical abuse" means any act or conduct which is of such a nature as to cause bodily`
  line `pain, harm, or danger to life, limb, or health or impair the health or development of the aggrieved`
  line `person and includes assault, criminal intimidation and criminal force;`
  line
  line `(ii) "sexual abuse" includes any conduct of a sexual nature that abuses, humiliates, degrades`
  line `or otherwise violates the dignity of woman;`
  line
  line `(iii) "verbal and emotional abuse" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) insults, ridicule, humiliation, name calling and insults or ridicule specially with regard`
  line `to not having a child or a male child; and`
  line
  line `(b) repeated threats to cause physical pain to any person in whom the aggrieved person is`
  line interested;
  line
  line `(iv) "economic abuse" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) deprivation of all or any economic or financial resources to which the aggrieved`
  line `person is entitled under any law or custom whether payable under an order of a court or`
  line `otherwise or which the aggrieved person requires out of necessity including, but not limited to, house hold necessities for the aggrieved person and her children, if any, stridhan,`
  line `property, jointly or separately owned by the aggrieved person, payment of rental related to`
  line `the shared house hold and maintenance;`
  line
  line `(b) disposal of household effects, any alienation of assets whether movable or`
  line `immovable, valuables, shares, securities, bonds and the like or other property in which the`
  line `aggrieved person has an interest or is entitled to use by virtue of the domestic relationship or`
  line `which may be reasonably required by the aggrieved person or her children or her stridhan or`
  line `any other property jointly or separately held by the aggrieved person; and`
  line
  line `(c) prohibition or restriction to continued access to resources or facilities which the`
  line `aggrieved person is entitled to use or enjoy by virtue of the domestic relationship including`
  line `access to the shared household.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purpose of determining whether any act, omission, commission or conduct`
  line `of the respondent constitutes "domestic violence" under this section, the overall facts and circumstances`
  line `of the case shall be taken into consideration.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12900)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Information to Protection Officer and exclusion of liability of informant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12900&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person`
  line `who has reason to believe that an act of domestic violence has been, or is being, or is likely to be`
  line `committed, may give information about it to the concerned Protection Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) No liability, civil or criminal, shall be incurred by any person for giving in good faith of`
  line `information for the purpose of sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12901)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Duties of police officers, service providers and Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12901&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A police officer, Protection`
  line `Officer, service provider or Magistrate who has received a complaint of domestic violence or is otherwise`
  line `present at the place of an incident of domestic violence or when the incident of domestic violence is`
  line `reported to him, shall inform the aggrieved person--`
  line
  line `(a) of her right to make an application for obtaining a relief by way of a protection order, an order`
  line `for monetary relief, a custody order, a residence order, a compensation order or more than one such`
  line `order under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) of the availability of services of service providers;`
  line
  line `(c) of the availability of services of the Protection Officers;`
  line
  line `(d) of her right to free legal services under the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987);`
  line
  line `(e) of her right to file a complaint under section 498A of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860),wherever relevant:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this Act shall be construed in any manner as to relieve a police officer`
  line `from his duty to proceed in accordance with law upon receipt of information as to the commission of`
  line `a cognizable offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12902)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Duties of shelter homes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12902&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `If an aggrieved person or on her behalf a Protection Officer or a service`
  line `provider requests the person in charge of a shelter home to provide shelter to her, such person in charge of`
  line `the shelter home shall provide shelter to the aggrieved person in the shelter home.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12903)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Duties of medical facilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12903&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If an aggrieved person or, on her behalf a Protection Officer or a`
  line `service provider requests the person in charge of a medical facility to provide any medical aid to her, such`
  line `person in charge of the medical facility shall provide medical aid to the aggrieved person in the medical`
  line facility.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12904)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Appointment of Protection Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12904&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, by notification, appoint`
  line `such number of Protection Officers in each district as it may consider necessary and shall also notify the`
  line `area or areas within which a Protection Officer shall exercise the powers and perform the duties conferred`
  line `on him by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Protection Officers shall as far as possible be women and shall possess such qualifications`
  line `and experience as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions of service of the Protection Officer and the other officers subordinate to`
  line `him shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12905)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Duties and functions of Protection Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12905&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Protection Officer--`
  line
  line `(a) to assist the Magistrate in the discharge of his functions under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to make a domestic incident report to the Magistrate, in such form and in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed, upon receipt of a complaint of domestic violence and forward copies thereof to the`
  line `police officer in charge of the police station within the local limits of whose jurisdiction domestic`
  line `violence is alleged to have been committed and to the service providers in that area;`
  line
  line `(c) to make an application in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed to the`
  line `Magistrate, if the aggrieved person so desires, claiming relief for issuance of a protection order;`
  line
  line `(d) to ensure that the aggrieved person is provided legal aid under the Legal Services Authorities`
  line `Act, 1987 (39 of 1987) and make available free of cost the prescribed form in which a complaint is to`
  line `be made;`
  line
  line `(e) to maintain a list of all service providers providing legal aid or counselling, shelter homes and`
  line `medical facilities in a local area within the jurisdiction of the Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(f) to make available a safe shelter home, if the aggrieved person so requires and forward a copy`
  line `of his report of having lodged the aggrieved person in a shelter home to the police station and the`
  line `Magistrate having jurisdiction in the area where the shelter home is situated;`
  line
  line `(g) to get the aggrieved person medically examined, if she has sustained bodily injuries and`
  line `forward a copy of the medical report to the police station and the Magistrate having jurisdiction in the`
  line `area where the domestic violence is alleged to have been taken place;`
  line
  line `(h) to ensure that the order for monetary relief under section 20 is complied with and executed, in`
  line `accordance with the procedure prescribed under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(i) to perform such other duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Protection Officer shall be under the control and supervision of the Magistrate, and shall`
  line `perform the duties imposed on him by the Magistrate and the Government by, or under, this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12906)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Service providers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12906&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such rules as may be made in this behalf, any voluntary`
  line `association registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) or a company registered`
  line `under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or any other law for the time being in force with the objective`
  line `of protecting the rights and interests of women by any lawful means including providing of legal aid,`
  line `medical, financial or other assistance shall register itself with the State Government as a service provider`
  line `for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A service provider registered under sub-section (1) shall have the power to--`
  line
  line `(a) record the domestic incident report in the prescribed form if the aggrieved person so desires`
  line `and forward a copy thereof to the Magistrate and the Protection Officer having jurisdiction in the area`
  line `where the domestic violence took place;`
  line
  line `(b) get the aggrieved person medically examined and forward a copy of the medical repot to the`
  line `Protection Officer and the police station within the local limits of which the domestic violence took`
  line place;
  line
  line `(c) ensure that the aggrieved person is provided shelter in a shelter home, if she so requires and`
  line `forward a report of the lodging of the aggrieved person in the shelter home to the police station within`
  line `the local limits of which the domestic violence took place.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against any service provider or any`
  line `member of the service provider who is, or who is deemed to be, acting or purporting to act under this Act,`
  line `for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in the exercise of powers or discharge of`
  line `functions under this Act towards the prevention of the commission of domestic violence.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12907)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Duties of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12907&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government and every State Government, shall take all`
  line `measures to ensure that--`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of this Act are given wide publicity through public media including the`
  line `television, radio and the print media at regular intervals;`
  line
  line `(b) the Central Government and State Government officers including the police officers and the`
  line `members of the judicial services are given periodic sensitization and awareness training on the issues`
  line `addressed by this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) effective co-ordination between the services provided by concerned Ministries and`
  line `Departments dealing with law, home affairs including law and order, health and human resources to`
  line `address issues of domestic violence is established and periodical review of the same is conducted;`
  line
  line `(d) protocols for the various Ministries concerned with the delivery of services to women under`
  line `this Act including the courts are prepared and put in place.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12908)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Application to Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12908&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) An aggrieved person or a Protection Officer or any other person`
  line `on behalf of the aggrieved person may present an application to the Magistrate seeking one or more`
  line `reliefs under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that before passing any order on such application, the Magistrate shall take into`
  line `consideration any domestic incident report received by him from the Protection Officer or the service`
  line provider.
  line
  line `(2) The relief sought for under sub-section (1) may include a relief for issuance of an order for`
  line `payment of compensation or damages without prejudice to the right of such person to institute a suit for`
  line `compensation or damages for the injuries caused by the acts of domestic violence committed by the`
  line `respondent:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a decree for any amount as compensation or damages has been passed by any`
  line `court in favour of the aggrieved person, the amount, if any, paid or payable in pursuance of the order`
  line `made by the Magistrate under this Act shall be set off against the amount payable under such decree and`
  line `the decree shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, be executable for the balance amount, if any, left after such set`
  line off.
  line
  line `(3) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and contain such particulars as may`
  line `be prescribed or as nearly as possible thereto.`
  line
  line `(4) The Magistrate shall fix the first date of hearing, which shall not ordinarily be beyond three days`
  line `from the date of receipt of the application by the court.`
  line
  line `(5) The Magistrate shall Endeavour to dispose of every application made under sub-section (1) within`
  line `a period of sixty days from the date of its first hearing.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12909)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Service of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12909&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) A notice of the date of hearing fixed under section 12 shall be given by`
  line `the Magistrate to the Protection Officer, who shall get it served by such means as may be prescribed on`
  line `the respondent, and on any other person, as directed by the Magistrate within a maximum period of two`
  line `days or such further reasonable time as may be allowed by the Magistrate from the date of its receipt.`
  line
  line `(2) A declaration of service of notice made by the Protection Officer in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed shall be the proof that such notice was served upon the respondent and on any other person as`
  line `directed by the Magistrate unless the contrary is proved.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12910)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Counselling.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12910&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Magistrate may, at any stage of the proceedings under this Act, direct the`
  line `respondent or the aggrieved person, either singly or jointly, to undergo counselling with any member of a`
  line
  line `service provider who possess such qualifications and experience in counselling as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Magistrate has issued any direction under sub-section (1), he shall fix the next date of`
  line `hearing of the case within a period not exceeding two months.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12911)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Assistance of welfare expert.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12911&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding under this Act, the Magistrate may secure the`
  line `services of such person, preferably a woman, whether related to the aggrieved person or not, including a`
  line `person engaged in promoting family welfare as he thinks fit, for the purpose of assisting him in`
  line `discharging his functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12912)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Proceedings to be held in camera.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12912&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If the Magistrate considers that the circumstances of the`
  line `case so warrant, and if either party to the proceedings so desires, he may conduct the proceedings under`
  line `this Act in camera.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12913)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Right to reside in a shared household.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12913&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, every woman in a domestic relationship shall have the right to reside in`
  line `the shared household, whether or not she has any right, title or beneficial interest in the same.`
  line
  line `(2) The aggrieved person shall not be evicted or excluded from the shared household or any part of it`
  line `by the respondent save in accordance with the procedure established by law.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12914)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Protection orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12914&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Magistrate may, after giving the aggrieved person and the respondent`
  line `an opportunity of being heard and on being prima facie satisfied that domestic violence has taken place or`
  line `is likely to take place, pass a protection order in favour of the aggrieved person and prohibit the`
  line `respondent from--`
  line
  line `(a) committing any act of domestic violence;`
  line
  line `(b) aiding or abetting in the commission of acts of domestic violence;`
  line
  line `(c) entering the place of employment of the aggrieved person or, if the person aggrieved is a`
  line `child, its school or any other place frequented by the aggrieved person;`
  line
  line `(d) attempting to communicate in any form, whatsoever, with the aggrieved person, including`
  line `personal, oral or written or electronic or telephonic contact;`
  line
  line `(e) alienating any assets, operating bank lockers or bank accounts used or held or enjoyed by both`
  line `the parties, jointly by the aggrieved person and the respondent or singly by the respondent, including`
  line `her stridhan or any other property held either jointly by the parties or separately by them without the`
  line `leave of the Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(f) causing violence to the dependants, other relatives or any person who give the aggrieved`
  line `person assistance from domestic violence;`
  line
  line `(g) committing any other act as specified in the protection order.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12915)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Residence orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12915&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) While disposing of an application under sub-section (1) of section12, the`
  line `Magistrate may, on being satisfied that domestic violence has taken place, pass a residence order--`
  line
  line `(a) restraining the respondent from dispossessing or in any other manner disturbing the`
  line `possession of the aggrieved person from the shared household, whether or not the respondent has a`
  line `legal or equitable interest in the shared household;`
  line
  line `(b) directing the respondent to remove himself from the shared household;`
  line
  line `(c) restraining the respondent or any of his relatives from entering any portion of the shared`
  line `household in which the aggrieved person resides;`
  line
  line `(d) restraining the respondent from alienating or disposing off the shared household or`
  line `encumbering the same;`
  line
  line `(e) restraining the respondent from renouncing his rights in the shared household except with the`
  line `leave of the Magistrate; or`
  line
  line `(f) directing the respondent to secure same level of alternate accommodation for the aggrieved`
  line `person as enjoyed by her in the shared household or to pay rent for the same, if the circumstances so`
  line `require:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order under clause (b) shall be passed against any person who is a woman.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate may impose any additional conditions or pass any other direction which he may`
  line `deem reasonably necessary to protect or to provide for the safety of the aggrieved person or any child of`
  line `such aggrieved person.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate may require from the respondent to execute a bond, with or without sureties, for`
  line `preventing the commission of domestic violence.`
  line
  line `(4) An order under sub-section (3) shall be deemed to be an order under Chapter VIII of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and shall be dealt with accordingly.`
  line
  line `(5) While passing an order under sub-section (1), sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), the court may`
  line `also pass an order directing the officer in charge of the nearest police station to give protection to the`
  line `aggrieved person or to assist her or the person making an application on her behalf in the implementation`
  line `of the order.`
  line
  line `(6) While making an order under sub-section (1), the Magistrate may impose on the respondent`
  line `obligations relating to the discharge of rent and other payments, having regard to the financial needs and`
  line `resources of the parties.`
  line
  line `(7) The Magistrate may direct the officer in-charge of the police station in whose jurisdiction the`
  line `Magistrate has been approached to assist in the implementation of the protection order.`
  line
  line `(8) The Magistrate may direct the respondent to return to the possession of the aggrieved person her`
  line `stridhan or any other property or valuable security to which she is entitled to.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12916)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Monetary reliefs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12916&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) While disposing of an application under sub-section (1) of section 12,the`
  line `Magistrate may direct the respondent to pay monetary relief to meet the expenses incurred and losses`
  line `suffered by the aggrieved person and any child of the aggrieved person as a result of the domestic`
  line `violence and such relief may include, but not limited to,--`
  line
  line `(a) the loss of earnings;`
  line
  line `(b) the medical expenses;`
  line
  line `(c) the loss caused due to the destruction, damage or removal of any property from the control of`
  line `the aggrieved person; and`
  line
  line `(d) the maintenance for the aggrieved person as well as her children, if any, including an order`
  line `under or in addition to an order of maintenance under section 125 of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974) or any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The monetary relief granted under this section shall be adequate, fair and reasonable and`
  line `consistent with the standard of living to which the aggrieved person is accustomed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate shall have the power to order an appropriate lump sum payment or monthly`
  line `payments of maintenance, as the nature and circumstances of the case may require.`
  line
  line `(4) The Magistrate shall send a copy of the order for monetary relief made under sub-section (1) to`
  line `the parties to the application and to the in charge of the police station within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction the respondent resides.`
  line
  line `(5) The respondent shall pay the monetary relief granted to the aggrieved person within the period`
  line `specified in the order under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(6) Upon the failure on the part of the respondent to make payment in terms of the order under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Magistrate may direct the employer or a debtor of the respondent, to directly pay to`
  line `the aggrieved person or to deposit with the court a portion of the wages or salaries or debt due to or`
  line `accrued to the credit of the respondent, which amount may be adjusted towards the monetary relief`
  line `payable by the respondent.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12917)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Custody orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12917&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, the Magistrate may, at any stage of hearing of the application for protection order or for any other`
  line `relief under this Act grant temporary custody of any child or children to the aggrieved person or the`
  line `person making an application on her behalf and specify, if necessary, the arrangements for visit of such`
  line `child or children by the respondent:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Magistrate is of the opinion that any visit of the respondent may be harmful to the`
  line `interests of the child or children, the Magistrate shall refuse to allow such visit.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12918)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Compensation orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12918&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `In addition to other reliefs as may be granted under this Act, the`
  line `Magistrate may on an application being made by the aggrieved person, pass an order directing the`
  line `respondent to pay compensation and damages for the injuries, including mental torture and emotional`
  line `distress, caused by the acts of domestic violence committed by that respondent.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12919)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to grant interim and ex parte orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12919&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any proceeding before him under this Act,`
  line `the Magistrate may pass such interim order as he deems just and proper.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Magistrate is satisfied that an application prima facie discloses that the respondent is`
  line `committing, or has committed an act of domestic violence or that there is a likelihood that the respondent`
  line `may commit an act of domestic violence, he may grant an ex parte order on the basis of the affidavit in`
  line `such form, as may be prescribed, of the aggrieved person under section18, section 19, section 20, section`
  line `21 or, as the case may be, section 22 against the respondent.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (12920)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Court to give copies of order free of cost.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12920&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Magistrate shall, in all cases where he has`
  line `passed any order under this Act, order that a copy of such order, shall be given free of cost, to the parties`
  line `to the application, the police officer in-charge of the police station in the jurisdiction of which the`
  line `Magistrate has been approached, and any service provider located within the local limits of the`
  line `jurisdiction of the court and if any service provider has registered a domestic incident report, to that`
  line `service provider.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (12921)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Duration and alteration of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12921&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) A protection order made under section 18 shall be in`
  line `force till the aggrieved person applies for discharge.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Magistrate, on receipt of an application from the aggrieved person or the respondent, is`
  line `satisfied that there is a change in the circumstances requiring alteration, modification or revocation of any`
  line `order made under this Act, he may, for reasons to be recorded in writing pass such order, as he may deem`
  line appropriate.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (12922)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Relief in other suits and legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12922&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any relief available under sections 18, 19,20,`
  line `21 and 22 may also be sought in any legal proceeding, before a civil court, family court or a criminal`
  line `court, affecting the aggrieved person and the respondent whether such proceeding was initiated before or`
  line `after the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any relief referred to in sub-section (1) may be sought for in addition to and along with any other`
  line `relief that the aggrieved person may seek in such suit or legal proceeding before a civil or criminal court.`
  line
  line `(3) In case any relief has been obtained by the aggrieved person in any proceedings other than a`
  line `proceeding under this Act, she shall be bound to inform the Magistrate of the grant of such relief.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (12923)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12923&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The court of Judicial Magistrate of the first class or the Metropolitan`
  line `Magistrate, as the case may be, within the local limits of which--`
  line
  line `(a) the person aggrieved permanently or temporarily resides or carries on business or is`
  line `employed; or`
  line
  line `(b) the respondent resides or carries on business or is employed; or`
  line
  line `(c) the cause of action has arisen, shall be the competent court to grant a protection order and`
  line `other orders under this Act and to try offences under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any order made under this Act shall be enforceable throughout India.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (12924)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title Procedure.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12924&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, all proceedings under sections 12,18,`
  line `19, 20, 21, 22 and 23 and offences under section 31 shall be governed by the provisions of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall prevent the court from laying down its own procedure for disposal`
  line `of an application under section 12 or under sub-section (2) of section 23.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (12925)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12925&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `There shall lie an appeal to the Court of Session within thirty days from the date on`
  line `which the order made by the Magistrate is served on the aggrieved person or the respondent, as the case`
  line `may be, whichever is later.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (12926)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Protection Officers and members of service providers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12926&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Protection`
  line `Officers and members of service providers, while acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any rules or orders made thereunder shall be deemed to be public servants within`
  line `the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (12927)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Penalty for breach of protection order by respondent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12927&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) A breach of protection order, or of`
  line `an interim protection order, by the respondent shall be an offence under this Act and shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to twenty thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) The offence under sub-section (1) shall as far as practicable be tried by the Magistrate who had`
  line `passed the order, the breach of which has been alleged to have been caused by the accused.`
  line
  line `(3) While framing charges under sub-section (1), the Magistrate may also frame charges under section`
  line `498A of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or any other provision of that Code or the Dowry Prohibition`
  line `Act, 1961 (28 of 1961), as the case may be, if the facts disclose the commission of an offence under those`
  line provisions.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (12928)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Cognizance and proof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12928&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the offence under sub-section (1) of section 31 shall be cognizable and`
  line non-bailable.
  line
  line `(2) Upon the sole testimony of the aggrieved person, the court may conclude that an offence under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 31 has been committed by the accused.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (12929)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Penalty for not discharging duty by Protection Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12929&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `If any Protection Officer fails or`
  line `refuses to discharge his duties as directed by the Magistrate in the protection order without any sufficient`
  line `cause, he shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to one`
  line `year, or with fine which may extend to twenty thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (12930)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Cognizance of offence committed by Protection Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12930&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution or other legal`
  line `proceeding shall lie against the Protection Officer unless a complaint is filed with the previous sanction of`
  line `the State Government or an officer authorised by it in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (12931)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12931&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Protection Officer for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in`
  line `good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (12932)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Act not in derogation of any other law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12932&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of the provisions of any other law, for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (12933)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788&sectionId=12933&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00008_200543_1517807325788
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the qualifications and experience which a Protection Officer shall possess under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions of service of the Protection Officers and the other officers`
  line `subordinate to him, under sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner in which a domestic incident report may be made under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the form and the manner in which an application for protection order may be made to the`
  line `Magistrate under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which a complaint is to be filed under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(f) the other duties to be performed by the Protection Officer under clause (i) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 9;`
  line
  line `(g) the rules regulating registration of service providers under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which an application under sub-section (1) of section 12 seeking reliefs under this`
  line `Act may be made and the particulars which such application shall contain under sub-section (3) of`
  line `that section;`
  line
  line `(i) the means of serving notices under sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(j) the form of declaration of service of notice to be made by the Protection Officer under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(k) the qualifications and experience in counselling which a member of the service provider shall`
  line `possess under sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(l) the form in which an affidavit may be filed by the aggrieved person under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 23;`
  line
  line `(m) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
